description:
&lt;p&gt;The Horton General Hospital, Banbury is seeking a highly motivated individual to join the Shift Portering Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will requires the post holder to work a minimum of 40 hours per week on a 24hr Rota which includes nights, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates must be able to use their own initiative when working alone or as part of a team and must demonstrate excellent customer service skills, show a flexible approach to work and be willing to work when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of the shift based Portering Team, providing 24 hour Portering support to all wards and departments across site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will live within 30 minutes travelling time to the hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you read the Job Description and Personal Specification, as all applications will be scored against the required criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be provided for successful candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Simpson, Interim Porter Manager, Amanda.Simpson@ouh.nhs.uk, 01295 229261&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any further information please contact Amanda Simpson on the above telephone number or email anytime on Monday - Friday between 1.00 pm and 3.00 pm.&lt;/p&gt;
